Multiple linear regression analysis revealed that TA correlates with the Nx4 effect on stress-induced changes of amygdala RSFC. A significant cluster (peak t-value = 4.25; p = 0.002 cluster-level Family-Wise Error (FWE) corrected) was found for the right amygdala seed in the prefrontal cortex at MNI coordinates x = 0, y = 51, z = − 15 (Table 2). The region was identified as part of the pregenual anterior cingulate cortex (pgACC) and ventromedial prefrontal cortex (vmPFC) as shown in Fig. 3A and B. The resultant negative contrast of this association suggests that a higher TA score corresponds to a dampened stress-induced change of RSFC in the Nx4 compared to placebo condition, indicating a stronger Nx4 effect on stress response amelioration (Fig. 3C). For the left amygdala, no effect by TA level on the Nx4 effect was observed.Fig. 3
